<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Polifin half yr shr up 20 pct, div rises.</title>
<headline>Polifin half yr shr up 20 pct, div rises.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-02-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended December 25</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     48	   vs   40</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 12	   vs   10</p>
<p>    Attrib income	  263	   vs   218</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		  427	   vs   351</p>
<p>    Tax			163	   vs   132</p>
<p>    Turnover	     1,782	   vs 1,598</p>
<p>Div payable: April 25</p>
<p>On register: March 20</p>
<p>Full name: Polifin Ltd (industrial chemicals, oils and</p>
<p>plastics)</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts polled forecast half year earnings per share at 48.7 cents from 40 cents with a range of between 46.0 to 52.0 cents. The half year dividend was seen at 12.2 cents from 10.0 cents with the range between 11.5 to 13.0 cents.</p>
